	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f98317190330140>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=14&mid=98317190330140>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=98317190330140>RE: Necro pets and weapons</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=98317190330140#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Feb 26th 2:18 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Well, actually I'm a less advanced necro, level 35.&nbsp;&nbsp;But this is from some higher level friends, too.  I've heard many contradictory things about pets and weapons.  Perhaps some of the claims were accurate about the way things worked at the time, but got changed in one patch or another.<br><br>The most convincing is that pets no longer have their attack delay affected by weapons at all, as a nerf to the power of giving two fast daggers to a pet.  Their damage, under this scenario, depends on the level of the pet or the damage of the weapon: there's a formula based on level and another formula based on the damage rating of the weapon, and the pet's max damage is whichever is higher.  So giving a pet a rusty bastard sword (6/42) is better than giving it a fine steel short sword (4/23).  Or the same: at our levels, neither one will help with maximum damage.  <br><br>A crucial detail is that pets apparently do not get their dual wield attack unless they have a weapon in their off hand.  I could confirm that my 29 pet was dual wielding by giving it a slash and a blunt, of course, and seeing it usually slash with its primary hand but sometimes crush as well.  By contrast, it never says "hit" for a pet wielding only one weapon, only the damage type associated with the weapon, or the damage term for extra attacks such as bash or kick.  <br><br>So under this view, the only reason to give most pets any weapon at all is if you're giving them two weapons.  And then a rusty is just as good as a fine steel.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
